          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "AREA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Radiative widths were calculated by using ratios",
                "obtained in this experiment and values of 2g*Gn from",
                "REL-REF. Ratio for resonance was defined as",
                "   (Sn/Sgamma)*(EPSgamma/EPSn), where",
                "S- area under resonance peak,",
                "EPS - registration efficiency",
                "    for scattering (n) and capture (gamma) events.",
                "Values of efficiency of multidetector system obtained",
                "by statistical modelling ( code ROMSD):",
                "EPSgamma(4+)=74.2%, EPSgamma(5+)=76.5%,",
                "EPSn=32.5% for 165.7 - 202.6 eV,",
                "     33.3%     82.94 - 165.7 eV,",
                "     35.0%     31.14 - 82.94 eV."
              ]
